<subSubSection pageId="33" pageNumber="1166" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="33.[178,1085,1522,1603]" pageId="33" pageNumber="1166">
Etymology: The specific epithet (Latin, adjective: unarmed) alludes to the absence of ventral teeth on the ventral process of the aedeagus, one of the characters distinguishing this species from the similar 
<taxonomicName authorityName="HERMAN" authorityYear="2003" box="[619,742,1581,1602]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Lithocharis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="33" pageNumber="1166" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sordidula">
<emphasis box="[619,742,1581,1602]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="1166">L. sordidula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
